snippet.textDisplay:
The documentary Human Harvest was shown at universities and libraries in Virginia Beach, Richmond, Williamsburg, Henrico, and Charlottesville, all in Virginia, on October 17-21, 2019. A Q&A session followed each screening.

Canadian human rights lawyer David Matas and representative of Doctors Against Forced Organ Harvesting (DAFOH) Dr. Jessica D. Russo were present to answer questions from the audience after the screening.

The film covers the independent investigations carried out by David Matas and former Canadian Secretary of State (Asia Pacific) David Kilgour into the organ trade in China, where organs are taken without consent from prisoners of conscience, as well as documents the communist regime's crimes against humanity.

snippet.textDisplay: well good thing you said its the home edition at the start. firstly push up resting position can only be with your ass above and arms stretching. (you cannot get your hands up from the ground at all. you also have to keep a straight form and cannot "wiggle" whilst doing the push ups. when doing pull ups you cannot let go of the bar. resting can only be with you on top of the bar. and then running on a treadmill is not the same as running in a field or stadium. When jogging/running outside your body engages a lot more muscles and the breathing form is different. the ground wont be as perfectly even and itl be harder to run. so treadmill run does not count at all and might aswell just not of done it. sorry lmao. the video was definitely entertaining tho! ^^
